## Testing plan

This is the **final slice** and carries the full bundle gate set:
`build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`,
`impl-log-structure`, `state-of-world-structure`.

- `constructor-unit-tests` — `GroupsRoundTripTests.fs`: group member modes +
  lossless swap (AC‑G1), primary detector (AC‑G2), separate‑JSON round‑trip +
  schema (AC‑G3, AC‑H1).
- `ui-tests` — group on/off and `Set as primary` from the *Experiment* tab /
  context menu; undo/redo across placement, rotation, lock, group on/off,
  swap, detector change, multi‑level (AC‑K1); reset rotation / delete /
  reset view each undoable or confirmation‑gated with same‑row distinct‑colour
  Confirm/Cancel (AC‑K2).
- `ui-smoke` — the full app (constructor front door + ribbon + groups +
  detectors) boots and renders one frame per page/panel without throwing.
- `unit-tests` — legacy `BerremanTests` regression remains green.

(Worker: fill in concrete test names and counts as you implement.)

## Risks

High: Part K is cross‑cutting — every project‑mutating edit introduced in
slices 001–006 must now `push` a snapshot (History.fs:33) and stay
multi‑level (AC‑K1), without double‑pushing or pushing on no‑op edits. The
mutually‑exclusive vs multi‑select swap must preserve every member's stored
configuration losslessly (AC‑G1). The separate app‑data groups file
(G.3.2) must load/save and validate against its new schema independent of any
`.ocproj` (AC‑G3). As the final slice, a regression in any earlier area
fails the full gate set.

## Hand-off

This is the last slice of the arc. State‑of‑the‑world must carry the final
`gates:` baseline YAML block (legacy `berreman_unit_tests`,
`constructor` test count, and the UI test counts) so the arc closes with a
complete baseline. Record that every constructor action now participates in
`EditHistory` and that the groups/collections library lives at the per‑user
app‑data path — no in‑tree persisted operator state was added.
